# Website registered modal placement + form shells

## Placement

| Kind | Path |
|---|---|
| Shared (visitor + customer) | `website/src/app/ui/components/modals/` — e.g. `ConfirmModal`, `EntityPickerModal`, `DateTimePickerModal`, presentational `FormModal` chrome |
| Customer-only product form modals | `website/src/app/ui/components/customer/modals/` — e.g. `MeetingBasicsModal`, `MeetingParticipantAddModal`, `MeetingSubjectModal` |

Do **not** put customer-only registered modals in shared `modals/`. Do **not** bury registered modal Components inside feature folders like `customer/meetings/` — those folders own screens/rows/cards; modals open from helpers and register in `resources/configs/store/modals.ts`.

## Registration contract (ConfirmModal pattern)

1. One **Component** per modal identity in `initModalsProps`.
2. Open via `openModal(myInstance)(IDENT)({ ...typed props })` — data + small callbacks (`onSuccess`, `onConfirm`).
3. Own `useShallowForm` + `FormProvider` + shared `Form*` fields inside the modal when it is a write form.
4. Compose presentational `FormModal` for title/subtitle/card chrome when that chrome fits; do not register `FormModal` itself as a body host.

## Forbidden

- Generic `FORM` + `render: (close) => <Body/>` (or any JSX factory) stored on Redux modal state.
- Module-level “current body” hacks to paper over that pattern.
- Editing `ModalBase` for product form bugs.
- Customer meeting form modals under `components/modals/` or under `customer/meetings/`.

## Canonical

- Chrome: `website/src/app/ui/components/modals/FormModal.tsx`
- Customer forms: `website/src/app/ui/components/customer/modals/Meeting*.tsx`
- Registry: `website/src/resources/configs/store/modals.ts`
- Flows: `docs/platforms/website/flow-form-foundation.md`, `flow-customer-meetings.md` §6.4
